7101const Value* findValue(const char* str, unsigned int len)
7102{
7103 return CSSValueKeywordsHash::findValueImpl(str, len);
7104}
7105
7106const char* getValueName(unsigned short id)
7107{
7108 if (id > lastCSSValueKeyword)
7109 return 0;
7110 return valueList[id];
7111}
7112
7113const AtomString& getValueNameAtomString(CSSValueID id)
7114{
7115 if (id < firstCSSValueKeyword || id > lastCSSValueKeyword)
7116 return nullAtom();
7117
7118 static AtomString* valueKeywordStrings = new AtomString[numCSSValueKeywords]; // Leaked intentionally.
7119 AtomString& valueKeywordString = valueKeywordStrings[id];
7120 if (valueKeywordString.isNull())
7121 valueKeywordString = getValueName(id);
7122 return valueKeywordString;
7123}
7124
7125String getValueNameString(CSSValueID id)
7126{
7127 // We share the StringImpl with the AtomStrings.
7128 return getValueNameAtomString(id).string();
7129}
